frus:attachment.p:
Considering that this interposition of the Chargé
d’Affaires of the United States carries with it, in effect, an insult to the
national autonomy and the honor of the Assembly;

Considering that, above all, it is the duty of the
Assembly to preserve the dignity and decorum of the Nation and the good name
of this august body;

Considering that the Executive power has not
ordained the publication of the Constitution, and that this Assembly desires
that it be promulgated for the general good of the State;
